		},
		"tabLabel_2" : {
		  "type" : "label",
		  "position" : [24, 230],
		  "hAnchor" : "left",
		  "vAnchor" : "top",
		  "wrapWidth" : 192,
		  "fontSize" : 7.2,
		  "value" : "This update adds a new race, the ^orange;Spectwing^reset;! These are a race of winged insectoids with dazzling wings and sharp claws, lurking in dark caverns below.",
		  "zlevel" : 3
		},
		"tabLabel_3" : {
		  "type" : "label",
		  "position" : [24, 160],
		  "hAnchor" : "left",
		  "value" : "^orange;Detailed Changelog^#ffffff;",
		  "zlevel" : 3
		},
	  	"back_2" : {
          "type" : "image",
		  "position" : [16, 157],
          "file" : "/interface/scripted/arcana_updates/pheader.png",
          "zlevel" : 1
		},
	  	"tabLabel_4" : {
		  "type" : "label",
		  "position" : [24, 150],
		  "hAnchor" : "left",
		  "vAnchor" : "top",
		  "wrapWidth" : 192,
		  "fontSize" : 7.2,
		  "value" : "Added a new playable race, the ^orange;Spectwing^reset;.\n\nThe Spectwings are a race of winged insectoids, brought into physical form by cosmic rifts known as the Abyss. As natural abyssborn predators, they bear sharp claws, sturdy carapaces, as well as dazzling wings to attract prey.\n\nAdded ^orange;Scythes^reset;, a new weapon type that has lifesteal or inflicts certain unique statuses, but has a weaker damage output compared to other weapons.\n\nAdded a new environment, the ^orange;Abyssal Woods^reset;, replacing the main biome in Desolate planets.\nAdded a new village, the ^orange;Spectwing Nest^reset;, found primarily in Abyssal Woods or Illuminated planets.\n\n\nAdditions:\n\nAdded the following tenant types:\nLuye Heishe (Luye Tag)\nSeeker (Aurea Tag)\nArcanian Starfarer (Astral Tag)\nArcanian Mage (Runic Tag)\n\nAdded the following farmables:\nFluxroot (Superstorm Expanse, Neon Sea, Viridescent)\nTidenut (Shining Sea, Azure Sea)\nVirusac (Viridescent, Evoaquatic)\nBloody Gem (Animus)\nJungle Mango (Verdant)\nTatalot (Desolate, Nightmist)\nShellfruit (Bamboo Forest, Arcane Forest, various undergrounds)\n\nAdded the following factory machines:\n^orange;Refinery^reset;: An industrial machine for turning substances into refined materials and compounds, useful for producing fuel cells, synthweaves and plastic.\n^orange;Fuel Generator^reset;: A standard generator, useful for powering a large quantity of factory machines. Requires refined fuel cells to run.\n\nAdded Winter Feast foods! A big thanks to the contributors!\nAdded the Hall of Champions, a small area displaying statues of event contest winners within Lighthaven.\nAdded the Triple Decking Slam.\nAdded Corrodium Dagger, a weapon that inflicts Acidic Burning, which deals Poison damage based on target's maximum health (30 ~ 200 Poison damage per second).\nAdded new colors to the paint station.\nAdded new Titancorp crates.\nAdded a new boss theme, The Living Shadows, by Doranarasi\nAdded a new biome theme, Decline Region, by Doranarasi\n\n\nChanges:\n\nUpdated sprite and adjusted some attacks and the arena for the Dheral, and its in-game name is changed to the Erchius Herald. Its base health is increased from 1600 to 2100.\nSeveral armor sets now require either Synthweave or Nanoweave to craft. These can be found from dungeons or manufactured in Arcana's refinery.\nUpdated sprites for various tiles and crafting items.\nUpdated sprites for various furniture crafting stations & Exousia bookcase.\nUpdated descriptions for some essences.\nIncreased amount of tech cards crafted in recipes, from 4 to 6.\nRenamed Elementalist's Anvil to Basic Anvil.\nRenamed Orion Tech cards to Optimized Tech Cards.\nRenamed Behest Dongles to Behest Circuits.\nRenamed Slipstream Composites to Synthweave, and changed some of its corresponding recipes.\nVerrostin tech cards are no longer obtainable. Recipes instead use optimized tech cards or verrostin components.\nReduced tile mining time for Magiwood and Kuromatsu themed tiles.\nReduced costs for crafting wired objects and EPP augments in the Tech Station.\nChanged attack combo and sprite for Tenebrosity.\nChanged rarity of most Luye furniture from rare to common.\nRenamed Illuminated Stars to Pale Stars.\nRenamed Desolate planets to Abyssal Woods. Desolate is now a sub-biome.\nRenatine Fragments and Sceantine are no longer obtainable.\nIntima Essence, Vile Essence, Aeon Essence, Fluorescent Beacons, Herbs and Regulus Cells are no longer obtainable.\nTech Station now requires 4 Copper Components, 1 Battery and 8 Silver Bars to craft instead of 4 Holosium Bars, 1 Battery and 6 Arcanium Bars, and can be crafted at the starting tier of the Magician's Table.\nAdded Elysian Blades, Floral Shield and Arioforged Shield to early-game Arcana rare treasure pools.\nAdded Tailor Contract to the recruitment board's default contracts.\nAdded a teleporter to the Lighthaven training room.\nAdded an info text to the relics menu.\n\nReduced Aeon Timepiece's base health from 9100 to 9000. It no longer drops Aeon Essence, and instead drops 12 Aeon Leaf. (1 Aeon Leaf is required to craft 1 Nullatus Bar or 1 Aeon Sigil, 3 are needed to craft the Aeon Armor Set.)\nEvolapis and Cosmo Nemesis will now always drop 24 of their respective boss drops, as opposed of 16~22. (21 is required for their respective armor sets, and more for their themed weapons.)\nDheral will now always drop 4 Lunar Insignia. (1 is required to craft 1 Nullatus Bar or 1 Lunar Sigil.)\nSolar Guardian will now always drop 4 Solar Medallion and 24 Solar Essence.\nReduced base damage for Corrodium Moon Blade from 37.4 to 36.4.\nCorrodium Glaive now inflicts Acidic Burning when a critical hit is triggered.\nIncreased base damage for Hangetsu Tanto from 30.6 to 34.2.\nIncresed enhanced state damage for Luxiant from 120 to 136.",
		  "zlevel" : 3
		}
	  }
	},
